<task id="041" project="sdap-bff-api-and-performance-enhancement-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Private endpoints for all services</title>
    <tags>infrastructure, azure, security, bicep</tags>
    <phase>4.2</phase>
    <estimate>8h</estimate>
    <status>pending</status>
    <parallel-group>Wave-4.2</parallel-group>
    <dependencies>040</dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    <goal>Create private endpoints for Key Vault, Storage, Service Bus, Azure OpenAI, AI Search, Document Intelligence.</goal>
    <context>With the VNet and subnets in place (task 040), private endpoints enable secure communication between the App Service and all dependent Azure services without traversing the public internet. This is a foundational security improvement that subsequent hardening tasks (045-047) and the public access disable task (050) depend on. Private endpoints are deployed alongside public endpoints initially to allow a phased transition.</context>
    <constraints>
      - Deploy private endpoints into snet-pe subnet (from task 040)
      - Create a reusable Bicep module for private endpoint provisioning
      - Configure private DNS zones for each service type
      - Do NOT disable public access yet — that happens in task 050
      - All 6 services must have private endpoints: Key Vault, Storage, Service Bus, Azure OpenAI, AI Search, Document Intelligence
      - Document rollback procedure for each service
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file path=".claude/constraints/azure-deployment.md" reason="Azure deployment constraints and Bicep patterns" />
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step id="1">Create infrastructure/bicep/modules/private-endpoint.bicep (reusable module)</step>
    <step id="2">Add private endpoints for each service</step>
    <step id="3">Configure private DNS zones</step>
    <step id="4">Verify DNS resolution from VNet</step>
    <step id="5">Deploy alongside public endpoints (don't disable public yet)</step>
    <step id="6">Test connectivity through private endpoints</step>
    <step id="7">Document rollback procedure</step>
  </steps>
  <outputs>
    <artifact>infrastructure/bicep/modules/private-endpoint.bicep</artifact>
    <artifact>infrastructure/bicep/modules/private-dns-zone.bicep</artifact>
    <artifact>projects/sdap-bff-api-and-performance-enhancement-r1/notes/private-endpoint-rollback.md</artifact>
  </outputs>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>All 6 services have private endpoints deployed in snet-pe subnet</criterion>
    <criterion>Private DNS zones resolve correctly from within VNet</criterion>
    <criterion>Public access remains active as fallback</criterion>
    <criterion>Rollback procedure documented</criterion>
    <criterion>Connectivity verified through private endpoints for all services</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
